1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA ยง7246, sub-ยง1, as amended by PL 2023, c. 544, ยง1, is further
3 amended to read:
4 1. Controlled substance. "Controlled substance" means a controlled substance
5 included in schedules II, III, IV or V of 21 United States Code, Section 812 or 21 Code of
6 Federal Regulations, Section 1308, except testosterone.
7 Sec. 2. Information concerning testosterone. Immediately upon the effective
8 date of this Act, the Department of Health and Human Services shall purge from the records
9 of the Controlled Substances Prescription Monitoring Program, as established in the Maine
10 Revised Statutes, Title 22, section 7248, all existing information concerning the prescribing
11 and dispensing of testosterone.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill excepts testosterone from the definition of "controlled substance" in the laws
1144 governing controlled substances prescription monitoring and directs the Department of
1155 Health and Human Services to purge from the records of the Controlled Substances
1166 Prescription Monitoring Program all information concerning the prescribing and
1177 dispensing of testosterone.
